```

The `Sidebar` component would need to accept a `streakCount` prop or use `useStreakData` internally. Given that `Sidebar` is a presentational component that receives `links` as props, the cleanest approach is to pass `streakCount` as a new prop from the parent (`Home.jsx` and `MyProfile.jsx`), which already have access to the user data.

**`client/src/components/ProfilePage/components/ProfileHeroSection.jsx`** -- Add `StreakBadge` in the profile name row, after the badge pill. This displays on the user's own profile:

```jsx
<div className="profile-name-row">
    <p className="profile-name">{userData?.name}</p>
    <VerifiedBadge badge={userData?.badge} size={22} />
    {userData?.badge && (
        <span className={`badge-pill ...`}>...</span>
    )}
    <StreakBadge streak={streakData?.current_streak} size="md" />
